- "Journey through the wild storms of transfer markets" metaphorically refers to the transfers a player makes between clubs; 
- "Navigators" are users who have interaction records with the player's transfers; 
- "Voyages" represent the dates of the transfers; 
- "Ports" metaphorically indicate the clubs; 
- "Seasons of their expeditions" signify the time frame of the transfers; 
- "Prices of their passage" refers to the transfer fees; 
- "Type of their travel" indicates whether the transfer is permanent or on loan; 
- "Mysterious tangent of their transfer ID" is a mathematical computation (TAN function) applied to the unique transfer identifier for each transfer.

- 'journey across the seas' refers to international transfers;
- 'land Down Under' metaphorically refers to Australia;
- 'moved to new shores' implies that the player has participated in at least one transfer.
